\title{Gh Cli}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Enforces authenticated gh CLI workflows over unauthenticated curl/WebFetch patterns. Use when working with GitHub URLs, API access, pull requests, or issues.}

\subtree{
\title{gh-cli}
\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{Working with GitHub repositories, pull requests, issues, releases, or raw file URLs.}
\li{You need authenticated access to private repositories or higher API rate limits.}
\li{You are about to use \code{\startverb curl\stopverb}, \code{\startverb wget\stopverb}, or unauthenticated web fetches against GitHub.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\ul{
\li{The target is not GitHub.}
\li{Plain local git operations already solve the task.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Guidance}
\p{Prefer the authenticated \code{\startverb gh\stopverb} CLI over raw HTTP fetches for GitHub content. In particular:}

\ul{
\li{Prefer \code{\startverb gh repo view\stopverb}, \code{\startverb gh pr view\stopverb}, \code{\startverb gh pr list\stopverb}, \code{\startverb gh issue view\stopverb}, and \code{\startverb gh api\stopverb} over unauthenticated \code{\startverb curl\stopverb} or \code{\startverb wget\stopverb}.}
\li{Prefer cloning a repository and reading files locally over fetching \code{\startverb raw.githubusercontent.com\stopverb} blobs directly.}
\li{Avoid using GitHub API \code{\startverb /contents/\stopverb} endpoints as a substitute for cloning and reading repository files.}
}

\p{Examples:}

\pre{\startverb
gh repo view owner/repo
gh pr view 123 --repo owner/repo
gh api repos/owner/repo/pulls
\stopverb}

\p{For the original Claude plugin implementation, see:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb plugins/gh-cli/README.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb plugins/gh-cli/hooks/\stopverb}}
}
}
}